title: Appeal or search for a planning decision or notice

heading_context: Appeal or search for a planning decision or notice
Appeal a planning decision or notice
chunks.html_content:
Find out how you can appeal:

  • a planning decision
  • a householder planning decision
  • an enforcement notice
  • an advertisement consent decision
  • a minor commercial development decision
  • a listed building consent decision
  • a lawful development certificate decision
  • a high hedges decision
  • a tree preservation consent order decision

heading_context: Appeal or search for a planning decision or notice
Search for or comment on an appeal
chunks.html_content:
You can search for or comment on appeals made to the Planning Inspectorate.

You’ll need to create an account to comment on an appeal.

Search for or comment on a planning decision or notice on the Appeals Casework Portal.

You must have copyright permission to use any drawings or other documents.

You can upload Word documents, images or PDF files up to 15MB. Do not send web links to files - send the files themselves.

All files must be:

  • a single document, appendix or image
  • given file names that describe what they are
chunks.plain_content:
Appeal or search for a planning decision or notice
Search for or comment on an appeal
Before you start
You can search for or comment on appeals made to the Planning Inspectorate.
You’ll need to create an account to comment on an appeal.
Search for or comment on a planning decision or notice on the Appeals Casework Portal.
You must have copyright permission to use any drawings or other documents.
You can upload Word documents, images or PDF files up to 15MB. Do not send web links to files - send the files themselves.
All files must be:

  a single document, appendix or image
  given file names that describe what they are

Other ways to search for or comment on an appeal
chunks.html_content:
Contact the Planning Inspectorate customer support team to:

  • get help searching for an appeal
  • find out how to comment on an appeal by email or post if you cannot use the Appeals Casework Portal
